WEBVTT

00:01.768 --> 00:03.535
<i>(Carrie) It's always the same dream.</i>

00:03.537 --> 00:06.605
(Modern English's "I
Melt With You" playing)

00:06.607 --> 00:09.341
<i>I'm in the city...</i>

00:09.343 --> 00:11.009
<i>And I belong.</i>

00:11.011 --> 00:12.510
<i>Manhattan is mine.</i>

00:12.512 --> 00:14.613
(Horn blares, tires screech)
Hey, watch it!

00:14.615 --> 00:18.216
(Alarm beeping) <i>But then I always wake up</i>
<i>the same old Carrie Bradshaw...</i>

00:18.218 --> 00:20.151
(Beeping stops)
<i>In Castlebury, Connecticut.</i>

00:20.153 --> 00:21.653
(Liquid sloshes)

00:24.658 --> 00:27.892
♪ Using all my breath

00:27.894 --> 00:29.728
<i>They say to key to being a writer</i>

00:29.730 --> 00:32.464
<i>is figuring out who you are,</i>
<i>finding your voice.</i>

00:32.466 --> 00:34.265
Aah!

00:34.267 --> 00:35.467
<i>Well, that seemed to be the only thing</i>

00:35.469 --> 00:37.235
<i>I had found that day.</i>

00:37.237 --> 00:40.138
Where is it? Please, please.

00:40.140 --> 00:41.272
Dorrit!

00:41.274 --> 00:42.907
Where's the purse?

00:42.909 --> 00:44.943
What purse?
Give me a break, Dorrit.

00:44.945 --> 00:47.612
You know exactly which purse
I'm talking about. Mom's purse.

00:47.614 --> 00:50.982
♪ I'll stop the world
and melt with you ♪

00:50.984 --> 00:53.351
You can't go through my stuff. Don't.

00:53.353 --> 00:55.286
You have pot?

00:55.288 --> 00:57.022
Your friends smoke pot.

00:57.024 --> 00:58.356
You're 14.
So?

00:58.358 --> 01:00.659
So if dad finds out,
he's going to kill you.

01:00.661 --> 01:03.261
So you better not tell him.
Well, it'd serve you right if I did.

01:03.263 --> 01:04.361
You're such a tattletale.

01:04.364 --> 01:05.797
I'm sorry I have a life, and you don't.

01:05.799 --> 01:06.865
Oh, is that way you're always spying on me,

01:06.867 --> 01:08.033
listening to my phone conversations?

01:08.035 --> 01:09.501
Do not!
Do too!

01:09.503 --> 01:11.136
(Talking Heads' "Burning Down
The House" playing)

01:11.138 --> 01:12.504
(Both arguing indistinctly) 
♪ Watch out

01:12.506 --> 01:15.273
<i>The year? 1984.</i>

01:15.275 --> 01:16.775
<i>Romance novels were all the rage.</i>

01:16.777 --> 01:18.410
<i>We had an actor for president,</i>

01:18.412 --> 01:19.944
<i>and most people could say</i>
<i>they were better off now</i>

01:19.946 --> 01:22.113
<i>than they were four years ago...</i>

01:22.115 --> 01:24.182
<i>Except us.</i>

01:24.184 --> 01:25.817
<i>Four years ago, we had our mom,</i>

01:25.819 --> 01:28.253
<i>and three months ago,</i>
<i>we lost her to cancer.</i>

01:28.255 --> 01:30.588
<i>Things were definitely not better.</i>

01:30.590 --> 01:32.090
Give me back my purse, Dorrit!

01:32.092 --> 01:33.158
Aah!
Ow!

01:33.160 --> 01:35.260
God, what the hell is going on in here?!

01:35.262 --> 01:36.695
She bit me!
She's going through my stuff!

01:36.697 --> 01:38.096
We do not have time for this.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.564
You both have to be in school
in half an hour, all right?

01:39.566 --> 01:40.899
Carrie, go on and get dressed.

01:40.901 --> 01:42.600
I know you took it.
Go.

01:42.602 --> 01:45.970
You can't be late on
your first day. And, Dorrit...

01:47.106 --> 01:50.108
That is... way too much
eye makeup.

01:50.110 --> 01:52.744
♪ Time for jumping overboard

01:56.649 --> 01:58.316
Carrie...

01:58.318 --> 02:00.952
You're the older one.
You can't take the bait.

02:00.954 --> 02:02.554
I have teeth marks on my arm.

02:02.556 --> 02:04.622
I know that Dorrit can be difficult.

02:04.624 --> 02:08.158
But... your mom would want
you two to get along.

02:08.161 --> 02:11.296
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

02:11.298 --> 02:13.631
All right? So whatever you two
were fighting about,

02:13.633 --> 02:15.200
it's not worth it.

02:15.202 --> 02:17.702
She stole mom's purse.

02:17.704 --> 02:19.771
You don't know that.

02:21.107 --> 02:24.342
I can't go to school
without the purse, dad.

02:24.344 --> 02:26.544
You're going to school.
I don't have anything to wear.

02:26.546 --> 02:27.746
Come on.

02:27.748 --> 02:29.814
You've got a whole floor full of clothing.
No.

02:29.816 --> 02:32.484
Mom used to take me shopping for an outfit.

02:32.486 --> 02:35.086
It was--was a thing we did, you know?

02:35.088 --> 02:36.955
Back-to-school clothes?

02:36.957 --> 02:40.792
(Sighs) Okay.

02:46.766 --> 02:48.433
Did you want <i>me</i> to take you?

02:48.435 --> 02:51.870
No. No, that was, um...

02:51.872 --> 02:53.304
Supposed to be mom.

02:53.306 --> 02:55.540
I see.

02:56.575 --> 02:59.577
I just... I need the purse.

02:59.579 --> 03:03.348
I-I need a piece of her.

03:03.350 --> 03:06.918
I have an idea.

03:06.920 --> 03:10.155
<i>My mother left us on Memorial Day,</i>

03:10.157 --> 03:12.423
<i>and that's what</i>
<i>this closet felt like--</i>

03:12.425 --> 03:14.759
<i>a memorial,</i>

03:14.761 --> 03:19.197
<i>a still life of our life without her,</i>

03:19.199 --> 03:22.867
<i>as if leaving it untouched</i>
<i>might somehow bring her back.</i>

03:22.869 --> 03:27.038
<i>We had been forbidden to enter...</i>

03:27.040 --> 03:29.374
<i>Until now.</i>

03:31.000 --> 03:37.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:48.260 --> 03:49.360
Uh, not that dress.

03:49.362 --> 03:52.664
She wore it on her last birthday.

03:52.666 --> 03:57.035
You could spill something on it
or rip it, you know?

03:57.037 --> 03:58.603
Uh...

04:09.215 --> 04:10.748
Really?

04:10.750 --> 04:14.352
Yeah. Just... try not to
let 'em get broken

04:14.354 --> 04:15.887
in your backpack.

04:15.889 --> 04:18.555
I'll be super careful, I promise.

04:18.581 --> 04:26.581
Corrected by honeybunny
www.addic7ed.com

04:26.899 --> 04:28.132
(New Order's "Blue Monday" playing)

04:28.134 --> 04:29.968
<i>The first day of school was something</i>

04:29.970 --> 04:32.203
<i>I usually found exciting,</i>

04:32.205 --> 04:34.672
but so much had changed for me.

04:34.674 --> 04:37.976
(Indistinct conversations)

04:37.978 --> 04:40.078
Hi! How was your summer?

04:40.080 --> 04:45.817
(Indistinct conversations continue)

04:47.052 --> 04:49.053
<i>As I watched everyone passing</i>
<i>around the news of the day</i>

04:49.055 --> 04:52.056
<i>like mono after a homecoming dance,</i>

04:52.058 --> 04:54.926
I realized that I was the virus
<i>no one wanted to get near--</i>

04:54.928 --> 04:56.828
<i>the freak who had lost her mom...</i>

04:56.830 --> 04:59.998
(Door squeaks)

05:00.000 --> 05:04.802
<i>Except for Donna Ladonna</i>
<i>and her minions, the Jens.</i>

05:04.804 --> 05:05.837
<i>Donna was just twisted enough</i>

05:05.839 --> 05:07.438
<i>to think a connection to tragedy</i>

05:07.440 --> 05:10.108
<i>would make her</i>
<i>that much more compelling,</i>

05:10.110 --> 05:12.243
<i>and she wouldn't be wrong.</i>

05:12.245 --> 05:16.047
Carrie, you poor girl.
Are you doing okay?

05:16.049 --> 05:17.415
Yeah, I'm fine.

05:17.417 --> 05:19.317
Okay, well, if you need anything--

05:19.319 --> 05:22.954
I mean, a shoulder to cry on,
fashion tips,

05:22.956 --> 05:27.892
maybe even a wand of mascara,
I'm here for you.

05:27.894 --> 05:30.995
I'll keep that in mind.
Thanks.

05:33.632 --> 05:35.233
You're such a good person.

05:35.235 --> 05:37.936
(Voice breaks) Thanks.

05:37.938 --> 05:39.537
And then there were my people--

05:39.539 --> 05:41.973
<i>my best friends</i>
<i>who loved me no matter what.</i>

05:41.975 --> 05:43.341
Bradshaw.

05:43.343 --> 05:44.442
Mouse.

05:44.444 --> 05:46.010
(Laughs) Oh!

05:46.012 --> 05:47.679
(Both laugh)

05:47.681 --> 05:48.913
I heart you, you know?
I know.

05:48.915 --> 05:50.281
I need it.

05:50.283 --> 05:53.251
Boob to boob, baby.
Hi, Maggie.

05:53.253 --> 05:54.652
Hey.

05:54.654 --> 05:56.321
Walt, nice sweater.
Is that the one from...

05:56.323 --> 05:57.822
The one Rob Lowe was wearing
in "Interview"?

05:57.824 --> 05:59.724
Nice.
How you holding up?

05:59.726 --> 06:01.592
Mm. I'd be a lot better
if I didn't feel like everyone

06:01.594 --> 06:02.660
was staring at me.

06:02.662 --> 06:04.228
Oh, please. No one is even looking at you.

06:04.230 --> 06:05.363
Believe it or not,

06:05.365 --> 06:06.798
I think Mags actually meant that
as a compliment.

06:06.800 --> 06:08.132
Mm-hmm.

06:08.134 --> 06:09.133
There is way bigger news today.

06:09.135 --> 06:11.736
I have to agree. New kid.
New guy.

06:11.738 --> 06:13.071
A junior like us.

06:13.073 --> 06:14.205
Ah, does new kid have a name?

06:14.207 --> 06:15.540
Even his name is cool.

06:15.542 --> 06:17.342
Sebastian Kydd.

06:17.344 --> 06:20.478
♪ Told me who you are

06:20.480 --> 06:23.881
♪ tell me how do I feel

06:23.883 --> 06:26.584
<i>There he was--the new kid,</i>

06:26.586 --> 06:27.719
<i>Sebastian Kydd.</i>

06:27.721 --> 06:30.755
♪ Those who came before me

06:30.757 --> 06:32.290
He's been kicked
out of three boarding schools--

06:32.292 --> 06:34.892
Deerfield, Exeter, and I forget where else.

06:34.894 --> 06:36.094
♪ From the past

06:36.096 --> 06:37.628
His parents finally had to give up

06:37.630 --> 06:38.696
and bring him home.

06:38.698 --> 06:41.666
♪ They will turn away no more

06:41.668 --> 06:43.267
They're totally rich.
He drives a Porsche.

06:43.269 --> 06:44.969
Mags, you do realize
I'm standing right here,

06:44.971 --> 06:47.505
and I'm your boyfriend?

06:51.577 --> 06:53.244
Hey, Bradshaw.

06:53.246 --> 06:55.747
Hey.

06:57.950 --> 06:59.517
Heard about your mom.

07:00.953 --> 07:02.487
Real bummer.

07:02.489 --> 07:03.888
Thanks.

07:03.890 --> 07:06.524
(School bell rings)

07:06.526 --> 07:07.658
I'll see you around.

07:07.660 --> 07:09.093
I can't get kicked out of another school

07:09.095 --> 07:10.395
this early in the year.

07:10.397 --> 07:14.198
(Indistinct conversations)

07:17.202 --> 07:18.703
So you have some explaining to do.

07:18.705 --> 07:20.471
(All giggle)

07:22.708 --> 07:24.375
Why did you hide this from us?
We need to know everything.

07:24.377 --> 07:26.778
I'm not hiding anything, I swear.

07:26.780 --> 07:28.413
Last summer, he hung out at the swim club.

07:28.415 --> 07:29.747
Why don't I swim?

07:29.749 --> 07:32.316
Because your hair would get wet
and your makeup would run.

07:32.318 --> 07:33.584
Hey, where's Walt?

07:33.586 --> 07:35.853
I told him I wanted it to be just us girls.

07:35.855 --> 07:37.522
Were you two fighting again?

07:37.524 --> 07:39.023
Come on. You guys are never gonna break up.

07:39.025 --> 07:40.291
You're forever.

07:40.293 --> 07:42.193
That's right, and the mouse and I

07:42.195 --> 07:44.562
would be a couple forever, too.

07:44.564 --> 07:46.764
Why do you have that look on your face?

07:47.566 --> 07:48.800
Mouse, did you meet someone?

07:48.802 --> 07:51.636
Are you breaking up with me?

07:51.638 --> 07:53.538
At the Page Program in D.C.

07:53.540 --> 07:54.605
I've been dying to tell you guys.

07:54.607 --> 07:55.606
So start talking.

07:55.608 --> 07:58.209
Seth. Seth Glassman.

07:58.211 --> 07:59.544
He's from Washington, started Princeton.

07:59.546 --> 08:01.212
He's a freshman.
(Gasps)

08:01.214 --> 08:03.081
I should date an older guy.

08:03.083 --> 08:07.218
He's amazing. So smart. I mean,
we'd stay up in the dorm rooms

08:07.220 --> 08:08.653
and we'd just talk about everything.

08:08.655 --> 08:11.355
(Gasps) And I'd wake up
in his arms and just think...

08:11.357 --> 08:13.157
That you got laid.

08:13.159 --> 08:14.892
Just because all you think about
is losing your virginity

08:14.894 --> 08:17.495
doesn't mean the mouse does.

08:18.864 --> 08:22.567
Wait. You lost your virginity to Seth?

08:22.569 --> 08:26.404
It was like putting a hot dog in a keyhole.

08:26.406 --> 08:28.973
(Laughs) Ow!

08:28.975 --> 08:31.642
It hurt so <i>bad.</i>

08:31.644 --> 08:33.277
And I just kept thinking, like,
when is this going to end?

08:33.279 --> 08:36.948
And luckily it did, because it
was over in two seconds.

08:36.950 --> 08:38.683
It wasn't like that for me at all.

08:38.684 --> 08:40.751
Wait. You and Walt had sex?

08:40.753 --> 08:43.453
Uh, I wasn't supposed to say anything.

08:43.456 --> 08:44.589
Walt won't be mad.

08:44.591 --> 08:45.823
No, he will.

08:45.825 --> 08:47.391
Just... swear you won't say anything.

08:47.393 --> 08:50.428
I won't. I swear.

08:50.430 --> 08:53.331
So... I'm the last virgin?

08:55.267 --> 08:58.402
It's no big deal, Carrie.
I mean, sex isn't everything.

08:58.404 --> 09:02.507
So... you don't feel
like it changed you?

09:02.509 --> 09:03.908
(Chuckles) It's weird.

09:03.910 --> 09:05.943
Like, I feel more confident,

09:05.945 --> 09:07.512
like I know stuff,

09:07.514 --> 09:10.581
but scared 'cause there's
something to lose.

09:10.583 --> 09:13.518
Are you in love with him?

09:13.520 --> 09:14.852
(Giggles)

09:14.854 --> 09:18.022
We should go on a double date.
Is he coming up to visit?

09:18.024 --> 09:19.790
Yeah, I mean...
<i>While I had spent my summer grieving</i>

09:19.792 --> 09:21.926
and letting go of my childhood,

09:21.928 --> 09:25.363
my friends were falling in love
<i>and entering adulthood.</i>

09:25.365 --> 09:26.430
Hey, we should go on a triple date.

09:26.432 --> 09:28.866
You should ask Sebastian out.

09:28.868 --> 09:31.068
Ask him to the new beginnings dance.

09:31.070 --> 09:33.004
Maybe he'll hot dog your keyhole.

09:33.006 --> 09:34.672
Delightful.

09:34.674 --> 09:37.041
(Laughs) That's just how I'll ask him.

09:37.043 --> 09:39.076
Well, if you do, then he'll
definitely say "Yes."

09:39.078 --> 09:40.244
(Laughs)

09:41.880 --> 09:45.016
<i>Virgin--</i>
<i>a sexually inexperienced woman,</i>

09:45.018 --> 09:46.317
<i>a blank slate unchanged</i>

09:46.319 --> 09:49.787
by any past intimate connection
<i>or experience.</i>

09:49.789 --> 09:51.923
<i>The uninitiated.</i>

09:51.925 --> 09:56.561
<i>Yep, that pretty much described me.</i>

09:58.130 --> 10:00.298
You stole my hiding place.

10:12.444 --> 10:14.445
You hang out here a lot?

10:14.447 --> 10:17.381
Yeah. Yeah, it's a pretty good escape.

10:17.383 --> 10:20.418
You had a lot to get away from.

10:20.420 --> 10:22.987
If only I could escape my brain.

10:22.989 --> 10:25.957
Do you ever-- do you ever just sit there,

10:25.959 --> 10:27.525
and--and the words and thoughts
are, like,

10:27.527 --> 10:29.860
happening so fast in your mind
that you just--

10:29.862 --> 10:31.696
you can't even understand them?

10:31.698 --> 10:34.165
Not really.

10:34.167 --> 10:35.566
(Chuckles) Oh.

10:35.568 --> 10:39.237
I wish I hadn't just said that, then.

10:39.239 --> 10:42.340
I think it's cool you have
so much going on in your head.

10:42.342 --> 10:44.175
You've been through stuff.

10:44.177 --> 10:47.311
Not many people here can say that.

10:47.313 --> 10:48.613
Can you?

10:48.615 --> 10:49.981
Who, me?

10:49.983 --> 10:53.184
Poor little rich kid whose mom
left with the tennis instructor?

10:53.186 --> 10:54.952
I'm just a cliche.

10:54.954 --> 10:57.121
Your mom left?
I'm sorry. I didn't know--

10:57.123 --> 10:58.256
Oh, don't worry.

10:58.258 --> 10:59.924
Our maid Luisa still
gets dinner on the table.

10:59.926 --> 11:01.759
Nothing's really changed.

11:02.794 --> 11:05.796
Nobody's better off without a mom.

11:07.866 --> 11:10.067
Uh...

11:10.069 --> 11:11.936
I'm sorry, Carrie.

11:16.708 --> 11:19.243
<i>It was hard to believe</i>
<i>it was only last year</i>

11:19.245 --> 11:21.479
<i>we had spent the summer hanging out.</i>

11:21.481 --> 11:23.914
I can't believe you
don't know Atari "Adventure".

11:23.916 --> 11:26.083
No way. "Space Invaders."
That's my game.

11:26.085 --> 11:27.351
I mean, come on.
You get to kill aliens.

11:27.353 --> 11:30.254
Oh, you're crazy.
No, "Adventure" is so cool.

11:30.256 --> 11:32.089
You have to get this magic chalice

11:32.091 --> 11:33.858
to a gold castle, and then
there's these dragons

11:33.860 --> 11:35.226
that are trying to kill you.

11:35.228 --> 11:37.862
So you're the princess who
slays their own dragons?

11:37.864 --> 11:40.564
Well, somebody has to.
Might as well be me, right?

11:40.566 --> 11:42.566
I'd slay a dragon for you.

11:42.568 --> 11:45.469
<i>Suddenly everything was different.</i>

11:45.471 --> 11:47.638
<i>I knew he was gonna kiss me, so I did</i>

11:47.640 --> 11:49.307
<i>what any scared 15-year-old girl would do.</i>

11:49.309 --> 11:50.441
Ohh!
Aah!

11:50.443 --> 11:52.810
Aah!
Oh, now you're in for it.

11:52.812 --> 11:55.880
No! Stop. Stop.

11:55.882 --> 11:57.214
Aah! (Laughs)

12:12.597 --> 12:14.932
<i>It was a moment</i>
<i>I wanted to last forever.</i>

12:14.934 --> 12:17.201
(Exhales) <i>My first kiss.</i>

12:19.237 --> 12:23.107
My, uh, parents are putting in
a pool at our house.

12:23.109 --> 12:26.010
It's almost done.

12:26.012 --> 12:29.113
Oh. (Chuckles) Cool.

12:35.754 --> 12:37.221
<i>Once he had his own pool,</i>

12:37.223 --> 12:39.657
<i>I knew I would never see him again.</i>
(School bell rings)

12:39.659 --> 12:40.925
<i>And I was right...</i>

12:40.927 --> 12:42.660
<i>Until today.</i>

12:42.662 --> 12:43.828
Do you still swim?

12:43.830 --> 12:46.597
Yeah. Yeah,
I really love it.

12:46.599 --> 12:48.466
I never swim.

12:48.468 --> 12:49.834
Really?
That's kind of a waste

12:49.836 --> 12:53.537
since you have a pool in your backyard.

12:53.539 --> 12:56.107
Hey, would you, um--
I should...

12:56.109 --> 12:58.642
You.
Me?

12:58.644 --> 12:59.777
Yeah.

12:59.779 --> 13:02.446
Me. Okay. Um...

13:02.448 --> 13:05.316
Would you, uh...

13:05.318 --> 13:07.017
Would--would you...

13:07.019 --> 13:09.520
Check it out.

13:09.522 --> 13:12.223
Would you wanna go to...

13:12.225 --> 13:15.393
(Exhales) Would you want...

13:17.028 --> 13:19.130
<i>Why was my father here?</i>

13:19.132 --> 13:21.298
<i>The last time I had seen
him in these halls,</i>

13:21.300 --> 13:24.201
<i>I lost the most important</i>
<i>person in my life.</i>

13:24.203 --> 13:26.303
<i>(Mr. Bradshaw's voice)</i>
<i>You need to come home.</i>

13:26.305 --> 13:27.505
<i>Your mom's unconscious.</i>

13:27.507 --> 13:29.073
<i>(Footsteps thudding)</i>

13:29.075 --> 13:30.674
<i>It won't be too much longer.</i>

13:30.676 --> 13:34.178
Carrie? Are you okay?

13:34.180 --> 13:35.746
Carrie?

13:35.748 --> 13:38.516
<i>(Footsteps thudding)</i>

13:39.651 --> 13:42.486
(Voice echoing)
Carrie? Are you okay?

13:42.488 --> 13:45.990
Carrie? Carrie?

13:45.992 --> 13:49.059
(Students murmuring)

13:49.061 --> 13:50.694
(Boy) Whoa!

13:50.696 --> 13:51.996
Give her some air.

13:51.998 --> 13:53.264
(Boy) Is she all right?
Kiddo?

13:53.266 --> 13:55.533
Kiddo, can you hear me?
Carrie?!

13:55.535 --> 13:59.470
(Crowd murmuring)

14:02.272 --> 14:04.105
(School bell rings) (Both) Bye!

14:04.107 --> 14:06.441
(Indistinct conversations)

14:06.443 --> 14:07.809
Thanks for keeping an eye on her.

14:07.811 --> 14:09.043
Of course, Mr. Bradshaw.

14:09.045 --> 14:11.012
I better head back in.

14:11.014 --> 14:12.847
Oh. I'll call you later.
Okay.

14:12.849 --> 14:14.415
Bye.

14:14.417 --> 14:15.817
I'm taking you home.

14:15.819 --> 14:17.018
Dad, I'm fine.

14:17.020 --> 14:18.486
You fainted.
I just got scared when I saw you.

14:18.488 --> 14:20.989
You know, the last time you were here...

14:20.991 --> 14:24.392
Yeah. Yeah, I'm sorry.
I should've--

14:24.394 --> 14:25.727
I should've told you
I was coming in to meet

14:25.729 --> 14:27.228
with your guidance counselor.

14:27.230 --> 14:28.263
Yeah, you should have,
and I don't need some shrink

14:28.265 --> 14:29.697
talking about how screwed up I am.

14:29.699 --> 14:31.499
That's not what we were talking about.

14:31.501 --> 14:34.736
Then what?
You've been through a lot,

14:34.738 --> 14:37.105
and we thought maybe
it might be a good idea

14:37.107 --> 14:39.574
if you had a change of pace,
a change of scenery.

14:39.576 --> 14:41.009
You're shipping me off to a loony bin.

14:41.011 --> 14:43.544
Some would call it that...
Or call me crazy

14:43.546 --> 14:45.013
for agreeing to this,

14:45.015 --> 14:46.648
but what about an internship?

14:46.650 --> 14:49.684
One day a week,
for school credit, of course.

14:49.686 --> 14:52.520
Like, work in an office?

14:52.522 --> 14:53.821
Where?

14:53.823 --> 14:56.424
My friend's law firm in Manhattan.

14:56.426 --> 14:58.626
Manhattan?

14:58.628 --> 15:01.262
No way! Aah! No way!
(Laughs)

15:01.264 --> 15:02.697
What would I be doing?
Do--do I need to type?

15:02.699 --> 15:04.532
Because I'm not very good at that.

15:04.534 --> 15:07.635
I just--I can't believe it.
I-I can't believe it.

15:07.637 --> 15:09.937
Okay, I guess--I guess
you really are feeling okay.

15:09.939 --> 15:12.640
Now, look, I know this all
sounds really cool, right? Yeah.

15:12.642 --> 15:14.309
But it's also a lot of responsibility.

15:14.311 --> 15:15.777
New York is an intense place,

15:15.779 --> 15:18.079
and you're gonna have to prove
to me that you can handle it.

15:18.081 --> 15:20.214
I will. I promise.
I'll be a total professional.

15:20.216 --> 15:23.618
(Sighs) Will I need a briefcase?

15:23.620 --> 15:25.653
Dorrit.

15:25.655 --> 15:28.356
I start my job tomorrow.
Can I have the purse back?

15:28.358 --> 15:31.025
I know you have it.
You mean your lame internship?

15:31.027 --> 15:32.293
Like I care.

15:32.295 --> 15:33.828
Please, can I have mom's purse back?

15:33.830 --> 15:37.165
<i>(Rock music playing over headphones)</i>

15:38.867 --> 15:40.802
Maybe you lost it.

15:40.804 --> 15:42.570
You won't mind if I look around.

15:49.445 --> 15:53.014
Get away from my stuff.

15:53.016 --> 15:55.183
(Clatter)

15:56.352 --> 15:57.552
(Snap)

15:57.554 --> 15:59.654
You're such a klepto.

16:07.329 --> 16:08.863
It's covered in nail polish.

16:08.865 --> 16:10.365
Oh--oh, my God.

16:10.367 --> 16:11.599
It's ruined.

16:11.601 --> 16:13.067
Why did you do that?

16:13.069 --> 16:15.269
I didn't mean to.
The bottle must have broke.

16:15.271 --> 16:16.237
You wanted to destroy it.

16:16.239 --> 16:18.139
No.

16:18.141 --> 16:20.808
I wanted something of mom,
and you got everything.

16:20.810 --> 16:22.810
No, I, don't.
You got the purse.

16:22.812 --> 16:24.412
Your 16th birthday.
The start of high school.

16:24.414 --> 16:26.714
I got nothing.

16:30.052 --> 16:33.054
<i>I never thought of myself</i>
<i>as the lucky one,</i>

16:33.056 --> 16:35.022
but I had precious extra years
<i>with our mom</i>

16:35.024 --> 16:38.025
<i>that Dora would never have.</i>

16:38.027 --> 16:41.596
(Sighs) You're okay, Dorrit.

16:41.598 --> 16:43.398
You're okay.

16:45.601 --> 16:48.870
Mom loved you.

16:48.872 --> 16:50.071
So much.

16:50.073 --> 16:52.306
I don't need your pity.

16:52.308 --> 16:54.842
I'm just trying to--
You think because you always acted

16:54.844 --> 16:56.177
like such a goody-goody
around mom

16:56.179 --> 16:58.913
that you can boss me around?
Well, screw you.

16:58.915 --> 17:01.349
You're pissed at <i>me?</i>
I should be angry at you.

17:01.351 --> 17:03.451
You ruined mom's purse.

17:03.453 --> 17:04.719
You know what? I'm glad I did.

17:04.721 --> 17:07.422
Now you can't have it, either.

17:12.761 --> 17:16.097
<i>I realized I had a choice.</i>

17:16.098 --> 17:18.900
<i>I could blame Dorrit,</i>
<i>or I could let go of my anger</i>

17:18.902 --> 17:21.669
<i>and still find a way</i>
<i>to hold on to my mother</i>

17:21.671 --> 17:23.271
<i>and to the purse.</i>

17:23.272 --> 17:26.907
(The Bird & The Bee's
"Material Girl" playing)

17:26.910 --> 17:30.845
♪ Living in a material world 
♪ material

17:30.847 --> 17:32.780
♪ living in a material world

17:32.782 --> 17:36.851
♪ 'cause everybody's living
in a material world ♪

17:36.853 --> 17:39.454
♪ and I am a material girl

17:39.456 --> 17:43.825
♪ you know that we are living
in a material world ♪

17:43.827 --> 17:46.360
♪ and I am a material girl

17:48.431 --> 17:52.166
♪ a material, a material

17:52.168 --> 17:53.901
♪ a material girl

17:53.903 --> 17:58.072
♪ living in a material world ♪ material

17:58.074 --> 18:00.641
♪ living in a material world

18:00.643 --> 18:03.144
(Mr. Bradshaw) Carrie, we leave
for the city in five minutes!

18:03.146 --> 18:04.312
You ready?

18:04.314 --> 18:05.513
♪ Material

18:05.515 --> 18:10.051
<i>You bet I was.</i>

18:12.553 --> 18:15.887
(The Three O'Clock's "Jet Fighter" playing)

18:25.131 --> 18:26.999
<i>Manhattan was a lot like my purse--</i>

18:27.001 --> 18:29.568
<i>damaged, and it had seen better days.</i>

18:29.570 --> 18:31.970
<i>But I wouldn't have traded</i>
<i>that purse for this moment</i>

18:31.972 --> 18:34.606
<i>for anything.</i>

18:34.608 --> 18:36.575
(Horn blares)

18:36.577 --> 18:39.344
(Indistinct conversations)

18:46.887 --> 18:48.186
Is this it?

18:48.188 --> 18:49.187
Yep.

18:49.189 --> 18:50.622
It's huge.

18:50.624 --> 18:51.890
(Brakes squeal)

18:57.164 --> 18:59.398
I can pick you up after work.
No.

18:59.400 --> 19:01.433
I'll take the 6:00 train
like we talked about.

19:01.435 --> 19:02.534
You said the woman I'm
working for can take me there,

19:02.536 --> 19:03.568
so I'm fine.

19:03.570 --> 19:04.770
All right, but if you change your mind,

19:04.772 --> 19:06.671
I can be here in an hour.
And don't forget.

19:06.673 --> 19:08.774
I'm going straight from
the train to the dance

19:08.776 --> 19:11.009
and home by curfew.
Good.

19:11.011 --> 19:13.178
How do I look?

19:13.180 --> 19:15.280
Like a young woman.

19:17.116 --> 19:20.018
How did that happen?

19:21.521 --> 19:22.821
You sure you don't want me
to walk you in?

19:22.823 --> 19:25.323
Dad, young woman, remember?
I got this.

19:25.325 --> 19:27.526
It's okay. You can go.

19:27.528 --> 19:28.760
I love you, kiddo.

19:28.762 --> 19:30.462
Dad.

19:30.464 --> 19:32.664
Okay.

19:32.666 --> 19:35.033
(Kim Carnes' "Bette Davis Eyes" playing)

19:35.035 --> 19:36.968
(Engine starts)

19:39.906 --> 19:41.773
♪ Her hair is hollow gold 
<i>I had arrived</i>

19:41.775 --> 19:44.109
<i>to the place where so many</i>
<i>before me had come</i>

19:44.111 --> 19:46.344
<i>to live out their dreams.</i>

19:46.346 --> 19:48.146
<i>I wasn't sure where the city</i>
<i>would take me,</i>

19:48.148 --> 19:50.282
<i>but I couldn't wait to find out.</i>

19:50.284 --> 19:53.418
<i>It was the beginning</i>
<i>of my Manhattan love story.</i>

19:53.420 --> 19:54.986
♪ Bette Davis eyes

19:54.988 --> 19:56.788
Oh! Ow.
Yo, watch it.

19:56.790 --> 19:58.890
Ow.

20:04.530 --> 20:06.531
Blue files are cases that were litigated.

20:06.533 --> 20:08.533
Green are out of court settlements.

20:08.535 --> 20:11.736
They must be filed separately,
but alphabetically.

20:11.738 --> 20:12.904
I can do that.

20:12.906 --> 20:14.139
Is this a big case?

20:14.141 --> 20:15.941
They're files from old closed cases.

20:15.943 --> 20:17.843
They'll be taken to cold storage.

20:17.845 --> 20:18.944
This...
(Sets down files)

20:18.946 --> 20:20.479
Is where you'll be working.

20:20.481 --> 20:21.713
Oh.

20:21.715 --> 20:24.182
Oh. And you get a half-hour for lunch.

20:24.184 --> 20:25.884
And may I suggest you go get
yourself a pair of stockings

20:25.886 --> 20:30.188
- during that time? - Of course. I-I fell,
and they ripped, and where would I--

20:30.190 --> 20:31.323
Try Century 21.

20:31.325 --> 20:33.391
Oh. And one more thing.
Yes?

20:33.393 --> 20:35.694
No personal phone calls.

20:37.730 --> 20:41.533
(Depeche Mode's "Just Can't Get
Enough" plays) (Horn honks)

20:56.015 --> 21:00.185
♪ When I'm with you, baby,
I go out of my head ♪

21:00.187 --> 21:01.853
♪ and I just can't get enough

21:01.855 --> 21:03.188
♪ and I just can't get enough

21:03.190 --> 21:05.357
In my years of playing dress-up <i>as a child,</i>

21:05.359 --> 21:08.894
I understood that what you wore
<i>could help define you.</i>

21:08.896 --> 21:11.730
<i>But in this store, I realized</i>
<i>you might even be able</i>

21:11.732 --> 21:13.665
<i>to change who you are.</i>

21:13.667 --> 21:15.333
♪ As we fall in love

21:15.335 --> 21:20.372
♪ and I just can't seem
to get enough of ♪

21:24.143 --> 21:26.511
<i>Maybe you could walk in here one person,</i>

21:26.513 --> 21:29.247
<i>a kid from Connecticut, and walk out...</i>

21:29.249 --> 21:31.283
Your bag! Aah!

21:31.285 --> 21:32.484
(Hangers clatter)

21:32.486 --> 21:33.418
(Gasps)

21:33.420 --> 21:35.754
Oh! (Laughs)
What the hell?

21:35.756 --> 21:37.155
Why'd you do that?

21:37.157 --> 21:38.723
Um, aren't you trying to steal my purse?

21:38.725 --> 21:41.226
No. Though I do wanna get my hands on it,

21:41.228 --> 21:44.429
but not to steal.
To shoot it.

21:44.431 --> 21:46.531
I don't understand.

21:46.533 --> 21:48.867
For a photo shoot I'm doing
for "Interview" magazine.

21:48.869 --> 21:52.037
You work at "Interview" magazine?

21:52.039 --> 21:54.406
Larissa Loughlin, style editor.

21:54.408 --> 21:55.874
Carrie Bradshaw. Mortified.

21:55.876 --> 21:57.075
(Chuckles)

21:57.077 --> 21:58.777
I'm doing this fashion shoot that's a cross

21:58.779 --> 22:00.145
between "A Midsummer Night's Dream"

22:00.147 --> 22:03.081
and "Scarface," and that
purse would be perfect.

22:03.083 --> 22:05.283
My purse? In "Interview"?

22:06.319 --> 22:08.286
That would be so cool.

22:08.288 --> 22:09.588
You like the magazine?

22:09.590 --> 22:12.991
Oh. That--that doesn't
even begin to describe it.

22:12.993 --> 22:14.492
And the one with Rob Lowe on the cover--

22:14.494 --> 22:16.094
Oh! He's so hot.

22:16.096 --> 22:17.929
I get it. You're obsessed.
Just come in.

22:17.931 --> 22:19.931
So...

22:19.933 --> 22:21.233
Do you work around here?

22:21.235 --> 22:23.435
Um, at long and Whitney?
The law firm?

22:23.437 --> 22:26.004
Oh, I slept with a guy from there once.

22:26.006 --> 22:27.906
Kevin... something or other.

22:27.908 --> 22:30.742
He was sexy...
In a suit-tie kind of way.

22:30.744 --> 22:33.011
You're not shagging your
boss or anything, are you?

22:33.013 --> 22:35.013
No.
Smart girl.

22:35.015 --> 22:37.282
Don't crap where you eat, Carrie.

22:37.284 --> 22:38.850
Doesn't sound very appetizing.

22:38.852 --> 22:41.720
(Laughs) You are funny.

22:41.722 --> 22:42.887
I can't believe you made that purse.

22:42.889 --> 22:45.290
How did you come up with the idea?
Oh.

22:45.292 --> 22:46.825
Necessity-- the mother of invention.

22:46.827 --> 22:49.794
You're quoting Plato?
Oh, I love you.

22:49.796 --> 22:51.630
(Chuckles)

22:51.632 --> 22:54.165
You look amazing.

22:54.167 --> 22:55.934
You wanna help me with something?

23:00.072 --> 23:02.440
(Alarm blaring)
Miss? Miss?

23:02.442 --> 23:03.842
Yes. May I look in your bag, please?

23:03.844 --> 23:05.010
Uh, sure.

23:05.012 --> 23:08.280
There's my receipt.
One pair of nude panty hose.

23:08.282 --> 23:10.148
Sorry.

23:10.150 --> 23:11.483
Must have been a false alarm.

23:11.485 --> 23:14.386
Thank you.

23:14.388 --> 23:17.555
(Horn honks)

23:17.557 --> 23:20.925
(Laughs)

23:22.161 --> 23:26.164
Oh, that whole innocent,
young thing you have going...

23:26.166 --> 23:28.867
You could come in handy,
miss Carrie Bradshaw.

23:28.869 --> 23:31.202
I'm gonna have to keep you around.

23:31.204 --> 23:32.704
I collect people, you know.

23:32.706 --> 23:34.072
What does that even mean?

23:34.074 --> 23:35.507
Some people collect art,

23:35.509 --> 23:38.076
or like my mother, porcelain frogs.

23:38.078 --> 23:39.044
(Chuckles)

23:39.046 --> 23:40.312
I collect people.

23:40.314 --> 23:42.113
I guess we're less creepy.
(Chuckles)

23:42.115 --> 23:43.348
Do you need money or something?

23:43.350 --> 23:45.016
No. Why?

23:45.018 --> 23:46.418
Because you stole.

23:46.420 --> 23:47.752
When I was a teenager,

23:47.754 --> 23:50.522
I used to steal lipstick
from marks and sparks.

23:50.524 --> 23:53.024
As an adult, I've just upped the ante.

23:53.026 --> 23:54.826
I like the thrill.

23:54.828 --> 23:57.629
I've never stolen anything before.

23:57.631 --> 24:00.665
You have to come out with me tonight.

24:00.667 --> 24:02.467
We're starting at Indochine.

24:03.703 --> 24:06.271
Oh, let me guess.
You've never been there.

24:06.273 --> 24:08.540
<i>I couldn't decide whether</i>
<i>to tell her the truth</i>

24:08.542 --> 24:10.675
<i>or create a life for myself--</i>

24:10.677 --> 24:12.510
<i>a life I wanted.</i>

24:12.512 --> 24:14.446
Uh, there's this guy at my office

24:14.448 --> 24:15.780
who I've been messing around with,

24:15.782 --> 24:17.882
and so I--
He always hangs out there.

24:17.884 --> 24:21.119
So screw him. He doesn't
own Indochine. We do.

24:21.121 --> 24:23.254
Meet me there at 7:00.
Do not put on those panty hose.

24:23.256 --> 24:24.556
You'll look like an old maid.

24:24.558 --> 24:26.091
Ciao!

24:26.093 --> 24:27.225
Ciao.

24:27.227 --> 24:28.626
(Woman) Oh, yeah! You!

24:28.628 --> 24:30.161
(Gasps)

24:34.433 --> 24:36.034
She gave me her card and everything.

24:36.036 --> 24:37.736
Okay, stop for one second
and just take a breath,

24:37.738 --> 24:38.837
because when I tell you this,

24:38.839 --> 24:40.805
you might start hyperventilating.

24:40.807 --> 24:42.006
Is it good or bad?

24:42.008 --> 24:44.175
Sebastian called here.
For you?

24:44.177 --> 24:45.310
For your number!

24:45.312 --> 24:48.713
Shut up. Shut up, shut up.
W--

24:48.715 --> 24:50.415
(laughs) Apparently, like,
his mom knows my mom

24:50.417 --> 24:51.549
or something like that.

24:51.551 --> 24:53.718
Anyway, he had my number,
and he called for yours.

24:53.720 --> 24:55.086
Well, what did he say?

24:55.088 --> 24:56.588
He asked if you were gonna be back tonight.

24:56.590 --> 24:58.390
I think he wants to ask you to the dance.

24:58.392 --> 25:00.825
Aah! Aah! I have to call my house.
I hope he got the machine.

25:00.827 --> 25:02.560
I swear, if Dorrit answers the phone

25:02.562 --> 25:05.864
and says something weird, I'm going to kill her.
Yeah, okay. Call home.

25:05.866 --> 25:08.166
Okay.
Bye. (Laughs)

25:08.168 --> 25:10.101
(Button clicks)

25:10.103 --> 25:12.270
(Keypad beeps)

25:12.272 --> 25:13.405
(Telephone rings)

25:13.407 --> 25:15.874
(Ring)

25:15.876 --> 25:18.042
Dorrit, will you answer that, please?

25:18.044 --> 25:19.377
(Ring)

25:35.928 --> 25:36.448
(Busy signal)

25:41.834 --> 25:43.134
This came for you.

25:43.136 --> 25:45.203
For me?

25:45.205 --> 25:47.138
Well, this must be a mistake.

25:47.140 --> 25:51.810
So you bought a dress but not stockings.

25:51.812 --> 25:56.147
It's a gift from my dad.
I have a school dance tonight.

25:56.149 --> 25:57.916
You're wearing that to a school dance?

25:57.918 --> 25:59.217
I would never.

25:59.219 --> 26:03.254
It looks like something
that singer would wear.

26:03.256 --> 26:04.923
You know the one.

26:04.925 --> 26:07.425
The one who--who takes Jesus' name in vain.

26:07.427 --> 26:08.493
Madonna?

26:08.495 --> 26:10.829
Yes. Her. So disrespectful.

26:10.831 --> 26:14.098
Anyway, I have to pick up
my son from soccer practice.

26:14.100 --> 26:16.134
My idiot ex-husband just told me.

26:16.136 --> 26:18.102
Are you gonna be okay getting
yourself to the train?

26:18.104 --> 26:20.438
Just promise me you'll
take a cab to the station.

26:20.440 --> 26:21.406
Okay. No subway.

26:21.408 --> 26:23.241
Yeah, I promise.
All right.

26:23.243 --> 26:25.643
Have fun.

26:25.645 --> 26:28.646
(Cobra Verde's "Temptation" playing)

26:28.648 --> 26:30.915
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

26:30.917 --> 26:32.584
♪ ooh, ooh, ooh

26:32.586 --> 26:33.718
(zip)

26:33.720 --> 26:34.886
♪ Ooh, ooh

26:34.888 --> 26:36.521
♪ ooh, ooh

26:36.523 --> 26:40.058
♪ heaven, a gateway

26:40.060 --> 26:41.226
♪ a hope

26:41.228 --> 26:42.393
♪ ooh, ooh

26:42.395 --> 26:44.662
♪ up, down, turn around

26:44.664 --> 26:46.164
♪ please don't let me hit the ground ♪

26:46.166 --> 26:47.632
♪ tonight I think I'll walk alone ♪

26:47.634 --> 26:49.167
<i>I wondered where this golden chariot</i>

26:49.169 --> 26:50.535
<i>would take me--</i>

26:50.537 --> 26:53.071
<i>to the New Beginnings Dance and Sebastian?</i>

26:53.073 --> 26:55.039
<i>Or to Larissa and a new world?</i>

26:55.041 --> 26:56.341
Where to?

26:56.343 --> 26:57.909
♪ Oh, you've got green eyes

26:57.911 --> 26:59.210
♪ oh, you've got blue eyes

26:59.212 --> 27:02.380
<i>It was a good question.</i>

27:02.382 --> 27:06.851
♪ Oh, it's the last time

27:08.903 --> 27:12.171
(Laid Back's "White Horse" playing)

27:14.274 --> 27:16.442
♪ If you wanna ride

27:16.444 --> 27:17.977
(sirens blaring)

27:17.979 --> 27:20.646
<i>I had kept my promise to take a cab,</i>

27:20.648 --> 27:22.114
<i>but my bitchy boss was right.</i>

27:22.116 --> 27:24.317
<i>This dress didn't belong at a dance.</i>

27:24.319 --> 27:28.354
It belonged here, in the
city, <i>and so did I.</i>

27:28.356 --> 27:32.491
(Indistinct conversations)

27:37.364 --> 27:39.465
There you are.

27:39.467 --> 27:40.933
(Gasps) And in the dress.

27:40.935 --> 27:42.268
Oh, it looks fabu on you.

27:42.270 --> 27:43.369
Thanks.

27:43.371 --> 27:44.737
Will I be arrested in it?

27:44.739 --> 27:46.539
Don't worry. I didn't
steal it from a store.

27:46.541 --> 27:48.374
Just our style rack.

27:48.376 --> 27:49.842
Carrie, this is everybody.

27:49.844 --> 27:52.311
Everybody, this is Carrie.
Hi.

27:52.313 --> 27:53.546
Hello.
Hi.

27:53.548 --> 27:54.847
That's Dominick.

27:54.849 --> 27:56.849
He's an artist who works
with found objects and wax.

27:56.851 --> 27:58.918
That's Cathy.
She's a fashion designer.

27:58.920 --> 28:00.119
That's...
<i>They were artists,</i>

28:00.121 --> 28:01.921
<i>musicians, writers,</i>

28:01.923 --> 28:03.489
<i>distinctly themselves</i>

28:03.491 --> 28:07.026
in a city that celebrated them.

28:07.028 --> 28:09.195
<i>(Kenny Loggins' "Footloose" playing)</i>

28:09.197 --> 28:12.365
<i>It was such a stark contrast</i>
<i>to the world I came from,</i>

28:12.367 --> 28:13.432
<i>where conformity is demanded,</i>

28:13.434 --> 28:16.369
<i>and the Donnas of the world rule.</i>

28:16.371 --> 28:19.271
(Laughs) Mags, you are so tipsy.

28:19.273 --> 28:20.806
I think we should get you home.

28:20.808 --> 28:22.508
Being the police chief's daughter

28:22.510 --> 28:24.944
doesn't mean you <i>won't</i> get kicked
out of school. Party pooper.

28:24.946 --> 28:26.812
I'm just trying to have some fun.

28:26.814 --> 28:28.047
Hey. Hey, new kid, new kid.

28:28.049 --> 28:29.615
<i>♪ I've got this feeling</i>

28:29.617 --> 28:31.283
We'll be right back.
(Scoffs)

28:31.285 --> 28:32.284
Good luck with that.

28:32.286 --> 28:34.854
You're here right on time.

28:36.491 --> 28:37.556
For what?

28:37.558 --> 28:39.058
For me, silly.

28:39.060 --> 28:40.893
<i>♪ I'll hit the ceiling</i>

28:40.895 --> 28:43.496
<i>♪ or else I'll tear up this town ♪</i>

28:43.498 --> 28:45.364
(Man) So what school did you go to?

28:45.366 --> 28:46.899
Uh, Castlebury High.

28:46.901 --> 28:48.734
No. I meant college.

28:48.736 --> 28:50.569
Mm. You don't need to go
to college these days.

28:50.571 --> 28:51.871
This city is all about the young.

28:51.873 --> 28:54.040
I mean, you're dead here
by the time you're 25,

28:54.042 --> 28:56.909
or living in the suburbs,
which is worse than dead. (Laughter)

28:56.911 --> 28:58.611
Oh, she should write something for us.

28:58.613 --> 29:00.546
Oh, I-I'm not really a writer.

29:00.548 --> 29:01.847
My mom used to write, though, in a journal.

29:01.849 --> 29:04.050
Are you for real?
Still has her innocence.

29:04.052 --> 29:06.318
Still talks about her mom and her sister.

29:06.320 --> 29:09.889
What's her name again?
Dorrit. She's in a rebellious phase.

29:09.891 --> 29:11.624
(Snickers) Aren't we all?

29:11.626 --> 29:13.092
(Laughter)

29:13.094 --> 29:15.861
I-I should make a quick phone call.
I'll be right back.

29:15.863 --> 29:17.663
(Telephone ringing) (Whispers) Come on.

29:17.665 --> 29:19.265
Come on, dad. Pick up.

29:19.267 --> 29:20.633
Please. Come on, come on, come on.

29:20.635 --> 29:21.767
(Ring)

29:21.769 --> 29:23.869
<i>While I was getting</i>
<i>no answer from my dad,</i>

29:23.871 --> 29:26.472
the mouse was getting an answer
<i>she didn't like.</i>

29:26.474 --> 29:29.575
Oh, hi. Is Seth there?
Room 215.

29:29.577 --> 29:31.377
He's still not there?

29:31.379 --> 29:35.047
Okay. Uh, thanks.
I'll try again later.

29:35.049 --> 29:36.415
Thanks.

29:37.718 --> 29:39.351
(Sighs)

29:43.757 --> 29:49.061
(Shannon's "Let The Music Play" <i>playing)</i>

29:49.063 --> 29:54.200
(Indistinct conversations, laughter)

29:58.673 --> 30:02.441
(Laughter)

30:03.944 --> 30:05.611
<i>♪ We started dancing</i> oh.

30:05.613 --> 30:08.280
<i>♪ And love put us into a groove ♪</i>

30:08.282 --> 30:11.350
(Giggles) I'm--I'm sorry.
I-I-I didn't know.

30:11.352 --> 30:12.852
Know we were gay?

30:12.854 --> 30:14.687
Yeah. Can I tell you a secret?

30:14.689 --> 30:16.555
I-I've never met anyone gay before.

30:16.557 --> 30:17.923
Of course you have.

30:17.925 --> 30:19.425
No. No one I know is gay.

30:19.427 --> 30:21.560
Oh, honey, someone you know is very gay,

30:21.562 --> 30:22.695
but they're just hiding it.

30:22.697 --> 30:23.763
Or don't know yet.

30:23.765 --> 30:25.564
Look for the hot guy who loves fashion.

30:25.566 --> 30:26.732
And hates sports.

30:26.734 --> 30:28.100
Oh, my God. It's almost midnight.

30:28.102 --> 30:31.036
Kiss me again.
It's almost midnight?

30:31.038 --> 30:32.171
<i>♪ He won't get away</i>

30:32.173 --> 30:34.907
I'm sorry. I'm leaving.

30:34.909 --> 30:36.408
Oh, it's early. The night's just beginning.

30:36.410 --> 30:38.511
No, I-I, um, have a thing
at my dad's in the morning.

30:38.513 --> 30:39.545
I gotta go.

30:39.547 --> 30:40.980
Okay. Mmm, mwah!

30:40.982 --> 30:42.281
♪ The groove he can't ignore

30:42.283 --> 30:45.918
♪ he won't leave you anymore

30:48.189 --> 30:50.156
<i>Maybe it was the champagne or the dancing</i>

30:50.158 --> 30:54.059
<i>or that I was out of breath,</i>
<i>racing for the last train.</i>

30:54.061 --> 30:56.462
<i>Or maybe it was the realization that</i>

30:56.464 --> 30:59.532
<i>I might have just lost</i>
<i>my innocence, my virginity,</i>

30:59.534 --> 31:01.634
<i>and not to the guy I had hoped,</i>

31:01.636 --> 31:04.270
<i>but to a different man--</i>

31:04.272 --> 31:05.805
<i>Manhattan.</i>

31:05.807 --> 31:07.640
<i>And maybe it wouldn't</i>
<i>respect me in the morning</i>

31:07.642 --> 31:11.510
<i>or even remember me,</i>
<i>but... I knew after tonight</i>

31:11.512 --> 31:14.313
<i>I would never be the same.</i>

31:14.315 --> 31:17.283
Thanks for picking me up, Walt.

31:17.285 --> 31:18.450
I would never let a lady walk home alone.

31:18.452 --> 31:19.618
(Giggles)

31:19.620 --> 31:22.254
Now I want details.
Every last one.

31:22.256 --> 31:25.357
Well, I met a girl who works
at "Interview" magazine,

31:25.359 --> 31:27.793
and she took me to this
restaurant, Indochine,

31:27.795 --> 31:30.896
and people were drinking
champagne from the bottle,

31:30.898 --> 31:33.666
and... (Laughs) I was drinking
champagne from the bottle,

31:33.668 --> 31:34.700
and...
Wow.

31:34.702 --> 31:37.937
I never saw anyone pay for anything.

31:37.939 --> 31:40.639
<i>We</i> drank a six-pack
of peach wine coolers.

31:40.641 --> 31:43.209
Oh. So the dance wasn't fun?

31:43.211 --> 31:44.543
The usual. Maggie got wasted,

31:44.545 --> 31:48.447
and Donna hooked her claws
into the new kid.

31:48.449 --> 31:49.548
Sebastian?

31:49.550 --> 31:50.616
Hmm.

31:50.618 --> 31:52.952
Oh.

31:52.954 --> 31:54.753
(Sighs)

31:54.755 --> 31:56.689
Speak of the devils.

31:56.691 --> 31:59.959
Oh. Uh... careful.
Huh?

31:59.961 --> 32:04.630
(Man) ♪ I used to give up everything ♪

32:04.632 --> 32:08.200
♪ there were no clouds up in the sky ♪

32:08.202 --> 32:09.435
Bradshaw?

32:09.437 --> 32:11.971
Yours truly.

32:11.973 --> 32:14.974
I didn't see you at the dance.

32:14.976 --> 32:17.142
I wasn't there.

32:17.144 --> 32:20.145
Oh.

32:20.147 --> 32:21.513
You two need a ride?

32:21.515 --> 32:23.816
Looks a little crowded in there.

32:23.818 --> 32:27.219
Look, this isn't what you think.

32:27.221 --> 32:29.622
Uh, it's exactly what I think.

32:29.624 --> 32:33.025
(Laughs) Sebastian, come on.
We have to go.

32:34.729 --> 32:36.929
You should go.

32:36.931 --> 32:37.997
I'll see you around.

32:37.999 --> 32:40.165
That's it?

32:40.167 --> 32:42.368
For now.

32:44.271 --> 32:46.739
All right.

32:53.680 --> 32:54.880
(Engine starts)

32:54.882 --> 32:57.950
<i>Maybe my night with Manhattan</i>
had <i>changed me.</i>

33:00.220 --> 33:05.457
Even though I felt vulnerable,
<i>it was like the mouse said.</i>

33:05.459 --> 33:09.695
<i>I also felt powerful,</i>
<i>like I now knew things.</i>

33:09.697 --> 33:12.398
Why can't I find the perfect person for me?

33:12.400 --> 33:16.068
You know, like Maggie is for you.

33:18.004 --> 33:21.240
I'm not sure she is.

33:21.242 --> 33:22.808
Does she know that?

33:22.810 --> 33:26.345
She knows that I wanna wait until I am.

33:26.347 --> 33:27.913
To have sex?

33:28.949 --> 33:32.318
You guys haven't?
No.

33:32.320 --> 33:34.286
<i>I didn't understand.</i>
<i>If Maggie wasn't a virgin,</i>

33:34.288 --> 33:37.957
<i>and Walt had said "No,"</i>
<i>who had said "Yes"?</i>

33:37.959 --> 33:39.892
I must be the only 17-year-old guy

33:39.894 --> 33:41.961
saying "No" to his girlfriend.

33:44.531 --> 33:46.365
Did your dad call the cops on you?

33:46.367 --> 33:47.800
(Carrie) What?

33:47.802 --> 33:49.835
Why would he do that?

33:49.837 --> 33:51.270
Dad, I-I'm--I'm here!

33:51.272 --> 33:52.805
I'm here.
I'm sorry I'm late.

33:52.807 --> 33:54.206
Uh, we ended up walking home.

33:54.208 --> 33:55.774
It's Dorrit.

33:55.776 --> 33:57.242
She's missing.

33:58.211 --> 34:00.616
What?

34:06.818 --> 34:09.018
Something horrible might
have happened to her.

34:09.021 --> 34:10.554
She's okay, dad.

34:10.556 --> 34:12.088
This never would have happened
if your mother was here.

34:12.090 --> 34:16.659
I will kill her when she gets home.

34:16.661 --> 34:17.893
(Door opens)

34:17.896 --> 34:19.129
(Door closes)

34:20.164 --> 34:21.197
Hey.

34:21.199 --> 34:22.766
Dorrit.

34:22.768 --> 34:24.935
Where have you been?

34:24.937 --> 34:26.570
Whatever. With friends.

34:26.572 --> 34:29.105
I tried to call. The phone
must have been off the hook.

34:29.107 --> 34:30.507
Because you took it off.

34:31.442 --> 34:33.109
Are you drunk?

34:34.011 --> 34:35.712
Do you know how worried we've been?

34:35.714 --> 34:37.514
You better start explaining yourself.

34:37.516 --> 34:38.581
Or what?

34:38.583 --> 34:40.050
You'll ground me?

34:40.052 --> 34:41.551
You're not my mom.

34:41.553 --> 34:44.788
I'm done.

34:44.790 --> 34:45.956
I'm just done.

34:45.958 --> 34:47.924
Do you think I like this?

34:47.926 --> 34:49.726
Worrying about you?

34:49.728 --> 34:52.362
And having to be the mature one?

34:53.331 --> 34:55.864
(Voice breaking) I would do anything.

34:55.867 --> 34:57.400
I would do anything to have mom back

34:57.402 --> 35:00.971
and just to be your sister
and not have to worry every day

35:00.973 --> 35:03.340
what might happen to you.
I just...

35:03.342 --> 35:05.709
Ugh! I can't take it!

35:09.614 --> 35:11.982
(Sighs)

35:11.984 --> 35:15.151
<i>(Rock music playing)</i>

35:19.724 --> 35:23.326
Kiddo.

35:23.328 --> 35:25.028
I'm--I'm sorry.
(Music stops)

35:25.030 --> 35:27.364
Don't be.

35:33.170 --> 35:34.237
You know...

35:34.239 --> 35:37.173
I saw a lot of your mother in you today.

35:37.175 --> 35:39.142
Because I lost it?

35:39.144 --> 35:42.779
(Chuckles)

35:42.781 --> 35:45.148
When you were little,

35:45.150 --> 35:46.449
and you'd do something awful,

35:46.451 --> 35:49.653
I would just look at your tear-stained face

35:49.655 --> 35:50.887
and I'd melt.

35:50.889 --> 35:54.157
I couldn't punish you.

35:54.159 --> 35:56.293
Your mother was tough.

35:56.295 --> 35:57.827
Yeah, I remember.

35:57.829 --> 35:59.729
When I did cartwheels in the pizza place,

35:59.731 --> 36:00.830
she wouldn't let me go

36:00.832 --> 36:02.766
to Valerie Weiss' 7th birthday party.

36:03.934 --> 36:05.568
And she had a moon bounce
in the backyard.

36:05.570 --> 36:08.738
Well, she wanted you
girls to be accountable,

36:08.740 --> 36:11.608
said it would make you good people.

36:11.610 --> 36:14.277
And now that's my job.

36:15.680 --> 36:19.182
I haven't wanted to do it.

36:19.184 --> 36:22.686
You girls have been
through enough as it is.

36:22.688 --> 36:26.156
But also, um...

36:26.158 --> 36:28.925
By taking on your mom's role...

36:31.495 --> 36:34.798
That means I would have
to admit that, uh...

36:36.467 --> 36:39.402
That mom's really gone.

36:42.139 --> 36:43.740
Yeah.

36:45.676 --> 36:48.111
But I have to.

36:48.113 --> 36:49.479
It's what your mother would have wanted,

36:49.481 --> 36:52.048
no matter how much it hurts.

36:53.384 --> 36:54.584
(Inhales and exhales deeply)

36:54.586 --> 36:57.987
She also would
have wanted me to ground you

36:57.989 --> 37:01.991
for coming in an hour past your curfew.

37:01.993 --> 37:07.263
So... no more going out
the next two weeks. Okay?

37:09.133 --> 37:10.333
Okay.

37:10.335 --> 37:12.268
Okay.

37:14.672 --> 37:16.573
You don't seem too upset about that.

37:16.575 --> 37:19.943
No.

37:31.155 --> 37:32.856
(Knock on door)

37:32.858 --> 37:35.358
(Footsteps approach)

37:37.695 --> 37:39.362
Mouse.
Hi.

37:39.364 --> 37:41.631
What's wrong?

37:41.633 --> 37:43.666
Are you okay?

37:45.302 --> 37:47.003
(Sighs)

37:48.773 --> 37:51.040
I think Seth is breaking up with me.

37:51.042 --> 37:53.042
Why? What happened?

37:53.044 --> 37:55.245
He hasn't called in two days.

37:55.247 --> 37:58.948
Well, that's nothing, right?

37:58.950 --> 38:00.917
I called a bunch.

38:00.919 --> 38:04.421
No, mouse.
How many times?

38:04.423 --> 38:06.990
(Chuckles)

38:06.992 --> 38:08.224
Too many.

38:09.794 --> 38:11.661
Well...

38:11.663 --> 38:16.166
Well, you know, maybe he's just studying?

38:20.104 --> 38:21.971
Yeah.

38:21.973 --> 38:24.407
How could he have...

38:24.409 --> 38:27.010
Had sex with me and treat me like this?

38:31.749 --> 38:32.916
Come here.

38:32.918 --> 38:35.452
(Crying)

38:35.454 --> 38:37.454
Oh, I'm sorry.

38:37.456 --> 38:39.322
(Whimpering)

38:39.324 --> 38:42.292
Love is something we wait for.

38:42.294 --> 38:43.827
<i>We imagine our first kiss,</i>

38:43.829 --> 38:45.728
<i>our first sex,</i>
<i>our first "I love you."</i>

38:45.730 --> 38:49.232
<i>But we never imagine</i>
<i>our first heartbreak.</i>

38:49.234 --> 38:53.937
Maybe because it's too painful
<i>to even imagine.</i>

38:53.939 --> 38:58.107
But in a way, the pain of love
<i>is what truly changes us.</i>

38:58.109 --> 38:59.642
(Greg Laswell's "Girls Just
Wanna Have Fun" playing)

38:59.644 --> 39:01.144
Are you sure, dad?

39:01.146 --> 39:02.812
I'm sure, kiddo.

39:02.814 --> 39:09.385
♪ Well, daddy dear,
you're still number one ♪

39:09.387 --> 39:15.024
♪ oh, girls, they wanna have fun ♪

39:15.026 --> 39:16.526
You should take this, Carrie.

39:16.528 --> 39:20.063
♪ Oh, girls, they...

39:20.065 --> 39:21.764
I think Dorrit should have it.

39:21.766 --> 39:24.734
Mom always loved you in green.

39:24.736 --> 39:29.305
♪ In the middle of the night

39:29.307 --> 39:36.479
♪ my mother says, "When you
gonna live your life right?" ♪

39:36.481 --> 39:39.449
♪ well, mother dear

39:39.451 --> 39:43.019
♪ we're not the fortunate ones

39:43.021 --> 39:44.921
♪ oh, girls, they...

39:44.923 --> 39:48.124
<i>It's the losing of love</i>
<i>that makes us who we are--</i>

39:48.126 --> 39:50.226
<i>the loss of a parent.</i>

39:50.228 --> 39:55.632
♪ Oh, girls, they...

39:55.634 --> 39:57.200
<i>Of your virginity...</i>

39:57.202 --> 40:03.473
♪ All they really want

40:03.475 --> 40:06.943
♪ those girls, they...

40:06.945 --> 40:09.779
Who you thought you might be...

40:12.082 --> 40:13.316
Nobody saw you, right?

40:13.318 --> 40:14.984
'Cause if your dad found out...

40:14.986 --> 40:16.853
He won't.

40:16.855 --> 40:18.821
<i>Of your innocence...</i>

40:19.823 --> 40:21.324
♪ Only hide her away

40:21.326 --> 40:25.762
<i>Those losses are perhaps</i>
<i>our first steps into adulthood.</i>

40:25.764 --> 40:27.730
<i>Life gets more complicated.</i>

40:27.732 --> 40:29.165
♪ But not me (Exhales)

40:29.167 --> 40:31.167
♪ I wanna be the one

40:31.169 --> 40:32.435
I thought you didn't swim.

40:32.437 --> 40:34.304
I don't.

40:35.539 --> 40:38.608
♪ Girls, they

40:38.610 --> 40:41.878
♪ wanna have fun

40:41.880 --> 40:43.146
♪ oh

40:43.148 --> 40:44.714
Is that how it's gonna be?
Yeah.

40:44.716 --> 40:46.749
All right.
Aah!

40:46.751 --> 40:54.751
Aah!
♪ It's all they really want

40:55.093 --> 40:57.226
♪ those girls

40:57.228 --> 41:00.330
Oh, my God.
Donna's gonna be so pissed.

41:00.332 --> 41:01.664
♪ It's all they really

41:01.666 --> 41:04.567
<i>But it's also filled with promise</i>

41:04.569 --> 41:07.503
and the possibility of opening
<i>your heart to new beginnings...</i>

41:07.505 --> 41:14.510
♪ Those girls, they wanna have fun ♪

41:14.512 --> 41:17.847
Are these...
mom's journals?

41:17.849 --> 41:19.816
They're blank ones.
She always had a few extras

41:19.818 --> 41:22.685
just in case inspiration struck.

41:22.687 --> 41:23.987
Can I keep them?

41:23.989 --> 41:25.688
Of course.

41:25.690 --> 41:27.991
Thanks.

41:27.993 --> 41:31.294
(Cyndi Lauper's "Girls Just
Wanna Have Fun" playing)

41:34.598 --> 41:37.600
<i>And new dreams in new places.</i>

41:37.602 --> 41:41.104
<i>The city was no longer</i>
<i>a fantasy. It was real,</i>

41:41.106 --> 41:44.007
<i>and I knew now I wasn't</i>
<i>searching for something</i>

41:44.009 --> 41:45.708
<i>or somebody here.</i>

41:45.710 --> 41:47.910
<i>I was searching for me--</i>

41:47.912 --> 41:52.148
<i>who I was, who I wanted to be.</i>

41:52.150 --> 41:54.417
♪ Oh, girls just wanna have fun ♪

41:54.419 --> 41:58.154
♪ just wanna, they just wanna

41:58.156 --> 41:59.856
♪ girls

41:59.858 --> 42:02.625
♪ girls just wanna have fun

42:02.627 --> 42:05.695
<i>Finding my voice wasn't gonna be easy.</i>

42:05.697 --> 42:09.799
<i>But for the first time in a long time,</i>

42:09.801 --> 42:11.768
<i>I thought it might be fun.</i>

